      "semantic_score": 0.100,
      "formant_ratio": 0.596,
      "token_count": 19,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " actively prevents people from learning from their mistakes. It prevents you from finding the root cause."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 97040,
      "t1_ms": 104560,
      "confidence": 0.9460,
      "quality": 0.9460,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 12,
      "et_rms": 0.0926,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.70,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.163,
      "formant_ratio": 0.631,
      "token_count": 24,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " But there is another way. A post-mortem is blameless if people have no fear of punishment or retribution."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 104560,
      "t1_ms": 112880,
      "confidence": 0.8762,
      "quality": 0.8762,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 2,
      "et_rms": 0.0934,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.79,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.61,
      "semantic_score": 0.294,
      "formant_ratio": 0.620,
      "token_count": 31,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " The trick is to focus on the situation, on the how and why something happens. And not to focus on the people, not on the who."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 112880,
      "t1_ms": 117280,
      "confidence": 0.9171,
      "quality": 0.9171,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 4,
      "et_rms": 0.1008,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.89,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.61,
      "semantic_score": 0.350,
      "formant_ratio": 0.633,
      "token_count": 21,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " But sometimes it's not easy to only talk about the how and the why of a situation."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 117280,
      "t1_ms": 123440,
      "confidence": 0.9227,
      "quality": 0.9227,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.1095,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.86,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.62,
      "semantic_score": 0.272,
      "formant_ratio": 0.589,
      "token_count": 25,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Sometimes a failure can be traced to a single individual. But even then, there are ways to talk about the why."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 123440,
      "t1_ms": 131680,
      "confidence": 0.9476,
      "quality": 0.9476,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.1017,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.71,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.59,
      "semantic_score": 0.280,
      "formant_ratio": 0.578,
      "token_count": 23,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " You could treat this human error as a systemic failure of the organization, of the team, of the process."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 131680,
      "t1_ms": 139440,
      "confidence": 0.9010,
      "quality": 0.9010,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 4,
      "et_rms": 0.1053,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.72,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.44,
      "semantic_score": 0.160,
      "formant_ratio": 0.531,
      "token_count": 21,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " There is something in the team or the process that made this person press this button believing it would not"
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 139440,
      "t1_ms": 146560,
      "confidence": 0.9359,
      "quality": 0.9359,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.1104,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.85,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.52,
      "semantic_score": 0.194,
      "formant_ratio": 0.515,
      "token_count": 32,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " bring the system down. And then the system was brought down. Is that a human error? Or is that the system is not designed well enough?"
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 146560,
      "t1_ms": 154160,
      "confidence": 0.8916,
      "quality": 0.8916,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 3,
      "et_rms": 0.1075,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.78,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.56,
      "semantic_score": 0.199,
      "formant_ratio": 0.578,
      "token_count": 26,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Or this person was never onboarded well enough? These are just examples, but you could treat it as a systemic failure."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 154160,
      "t1_ms": 159680,
      "confidence": 0.9050,
      "quality": 0.9050,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.1154,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.87,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.55,
      "semantic_score": 0.168,
      "formant_ratio": 0.572,
      "token_count": 22,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " This action made sense to this person. That person believed it wouldn't go wrong. But it did."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 159680,
      "t1_ms": 169280,
      "confidence": 0.8756,
      "quality": 0.8756,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 10,
      "et_rms": 0.0951,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.73,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.55,
      "semantic_score": 0.146,
      "formant_ratio": 0.645,
      "token_count": 32,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " What is wrong with the system or the process? Part two, prepare. Somebody should prepare and champion the post-mortem meeting for it to go efficiently."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 169280,
      "t1_ms": 175760,
      "confidence": 0.8682,
      "quality": 0.8682,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.0936,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.86,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.57,
      "semantic_score": 0.149,
      "formant_ratio": 0.642,
      "token_count": 26,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And there are two important ways to prepare. Write up a definition of failure and create a first timeline of the failure."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 175760,
      "t1_ms": 184560,
      "confidence": 0.9577,
      "quality": 0.9577,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0968,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.85,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.221,
      "formant_ratio": 0.565,
      "token_count": 35,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Let's talk about the definition first. To have an effective session, you want to describe the problem in an unambiguous way from the perspective of a client or user."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 184560,
      "t1_ms": 191920,
      "confidence": 0.9686,
      "quality": 0.9686,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 3,
      "et_rms": 0.0897,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.80,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.65,
      "semantic_score": 0.220,
      "formant_ratio": 0.615,
      "token_count": 26,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " You want to write about the impact of the problem and in what way they perceived the problem and what consequences the problem had."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 191920,
      "t1_ms": 200240,
      "confidence": 0.9162,
      "quality": 0.9162,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 9,
      "et_rms": 0.0923,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.78,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.63,
      "semantic_score": 0.291,
      "formant_ratio": 0.666,
      "token_count": 34,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " You don't want to focus on the cause of the problem right now. So what did you notice? Or worse, what did your client or user notice?"
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 200240,
      "t1_ms": 207680,
      "confidence": 0.9115,
      "quality": 0.9115,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 8,
      "et_rms": 0.0859,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.79,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.56,
      "semantic_score": 0.093,
      "formant_ratio": 0.699,
      "token_count": 27,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Let's look at an example. At quarter past two, users started seeing a 502 bad gateway error while trying to log in."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 207680,
      "t1_ms": 215440,
      "confidence": 0.9565,
      "quality": 0.9565,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 9,
      "et_rms": 0.0882,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.84,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.51,
      "semantic_score": 0.056,
      "formant_ratio": 0.655,
      "token_count": 24,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Users who cleared their browser cookies after seeing the 502 bad gateway error could proceed to user service while not logged in."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 215440,
      "t1_ms": 219920,
      "confidence": 0.9286,
      "quality": 0.9286,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.1057,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.78,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.53,
      "semantic_score": 0.137,
      "formant_ratio": 0.585,
      "token_count": 18,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And users who didn't attempt to log in at all didn't experience the failure."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 219920,
      "t1_ms": 225440,
      "confidence": 0.9782,
      "quality": 0.9782,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.1020,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.85,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.62,
      "semantic_score": 0.320,
      "formant_ratio": 0.591,
      "token_count": 29,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And notice that this definition didn't focus on the cause at all. That's something you want to figure out together as a team."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 225440,
      "t1_ms": 232800,
      "confidence": 0.9267,
      "quality": 0.9267,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0940,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.89,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.61,
      "semantic_score": 0.224,
      "formant_ratio": 0.665,
      "token_count": 29,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " The second way to prepare is to create a timeline of the failure from when it was reported, until when it was resolved in the end."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 232800,
      "t1_ms": 237920,
      "confidence": 0.9721,
      "quality": 0.9721,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 6,
      "et_rms": 0.1021,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.89,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.283,
      "formant_ratio": 0.634,
      "token_count": 30,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And you want to leave some room on the left so that you can fill in the cause as a team. Let's look at an example."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 237920,
      "t1_ms": 245840,
      "confidence": 0.9361,
      "quality": 0.9361,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 6,
      "et_rms": 0.0943,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.80,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.57,
      "semantic_score": 0.213,
      "formant_ratio": 0.646,
      "token_count": 33,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " I've got a very basic timeline here. The reported state is in the middle where the cloud alert was the first hint for our team that something was wrong."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 245840,
      "t1_ms": 252880,
      "confidence": 0.8170,
      "quality": 0.8170,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0980,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.86,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.56,
      "semantic_score": 0.199,
      "formant_ratio": 0.641,
      "token_count": 28,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And then afterwards, we quickly had a team meeting. Some people started pair programming, the PO in parallel, started informing customers."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 252880,
      "t1_ms": 261920,
      "confidence": 0.8803,
      "quality": 0.8803,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0880,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.79,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.47,
      "semantic_score": 0.235,
      "formant_ratio": 0.692,
      "token_count": 34,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " There was even somebody who updated the status page. And at some point, the pairing or whatever happened in the fix solved the problem and we could deploy the fix."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 261920,
      "t1_ms": 268400,
      "confidence": 0.9216,
      "quality": 0.9216,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 6,
      "et_rms": 0.0960,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.90,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.55,
      "semantic_score": 0.235,
      "formant_ratio": 0.647,
      "token_count": 25,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And that's the moment when it was resolved. Sometimes these timelines are a few hours or a few minutes at best."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 268400,
      "t1_ms": 276560,
      "confidence": 0.8696,
      "quality": 0.8696,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 11,
      "et_rms": 0.0893,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.86,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.198,
      "formant_ratio": 0.715,
      "token_count": 37,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And worst case, there are days or however long you took to fix it or however long from the cause until the reports there is, which could also be a long time."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 276560,
      "t1_ms": 280400,
      "confidence": 0.9037,
      "quality": 0.9037,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 8,
      "et_rms": 0.0935,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.88,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.162,
      "formant_ratio": 0.659,
      "token_count": 18,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Another way to prepare your post mortem is to ask everybody to read this article."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 280400,
      "t1_ms": 288640,
      "confidence": 0.9298,
      "quality": 0.9298,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0895,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.85,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.70,
      "semantic_score": 0.227,
      "formant_ratio": 0.665,
      "token_count": 32,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " I came across this a while ago and I absolutely love it. It's spot on, it discusses the real problems of team dynamics with post mortems."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 288640,
      "t1_ms": 292480,
      "confidence": 0.9017,
      "quality": 0.9017,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 5,
      "et_rms": 0.0738,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.71,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.56,
      "semantic_score": 0.333,
      "formant_ratio": 0.627,
      "token_count": 15,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " It's a recommended read. Part three, the post mortem."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 292480,
      "t1_ms": 301360,
      "confidence": 0.9446,
      "quality": 0.9446,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 9,
      "et_rms": 0.1012,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.84,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.163,
      "formant_ratio": 0.597,
      "token_count": 33,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " When running a post mortem meeting, I recommend to instruct the group first on how to choose their words carefully. I recommend to set the tone first."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 301360,
      "t1_ms": 311280,
      "confidence": 0.9638,
      "quality": 0.9638,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 8,
      "et_rms": 0.0901,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.83,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.57,
      "semantic_score": 0.250,
      "formant_ratio": 0.621,
      "token_count": 36,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " This is where you can explain to people how psychological safety works. This is where you can ask them to be very precise and careful with their words, to be very factual."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 311280,
      "t1_ms": 322480,
      "confidence": 0.9342,
      "quality": 0.9342,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 12,
      "et_rms": 0.0937,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.76,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.235,
      "formant_ratio": 0.614,
      "token_count": 48,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " If you haven't done this before, you can put these words on a slide and read them aloud as an instruction. This is a blameless post mortem. We're not here to blame, we're here to learn."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 322480,
      "t1_ms": 331960,
      "confidence": 0.9246,
      "quality": 0.9246,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 4,
      "et_rms": 0.0750,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.70,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.57,
      "semantic_score": 0.175,
      "formant_ratio": 0.639,
      "token_count": 26,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Psychological safety is the belief that you won't be punished or humiliated for speaking up with ideas, questions, concerns or mistakes."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 331960,
      "t1_ms": 346520,
      "confidence": 0.9347,
      "quality": 0.9347,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 16,
      "et_rms": 0.0934,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.78,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.238,
      "formant_ratio": 0.608,
      "token_count": 46,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " We will focus on the situation, on the how and why something happens. We will not focus on the people. We will work with the assumption that nobody has ill intent and we try to assume the most generous interpretation."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 346520,
      "t1_ms": 356840,
      "confidence": 0.9220,
      "quality": 0.9220,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 10,
      "et_rms": 0.0976,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.86,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.57,
      "semantic_score": 0.231,
      "formant_ratio": 0.654,
      "token_count": 43,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " After you've set the tone, you probably want to look at the definition of failures, everybody is aligned with what the problem looks like from the outside perspective and then you want to move to your factual timeline."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 356840,
      "t1_ms": 365000,
      "confidence": 0.9252,
      "quality": 0.9252,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 6,
      "et_rms": 0.0933,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.68,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.58,
      "semantic_score": 0.133,
      "formant_ratio": 0.554,
      "token_count": 30,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Show the timeline you made. Ask what is missing. Ask what is incorrect. See how you can move forward as a group from here."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 365000,
      "t1_ms": 388840,
      "confidence": 0.8398,
      "quality": 0.8398,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 20,
      "et_rms": 0.0963,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.83,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.248,
      "formant_ratio": 0.587,
      "token_count": 101,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Together you can add the missing steps, you can add the cause, maybe you can go back even further before this deploy. Sticky over here, there was even a commit, there was a decision made by a developer. This is ok to do, which in the end turned out to cause the failure. It was not ok to do because there was an assumption that was made. If you can trace it back all the way there, you can really find the root cause of the problem."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 388840,
      "t1_ms": 395840,
      "confidence": 0.9194,
      "quality": 0.9194,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 7,
      "et_rms": 0.0947,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.83,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.59,
      "semantic_score": 0.265,
      "formant_ratio": 0.563,
      "token_count": 30,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " It's important here to stick with the facts. If everybody agrees with the facts, only then you can move forward to the next phase."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 395840,
      "t1_ms": 409840,
      "confidence": 0.8968,
      "quality": 0.8968,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 9,
      "et_rms": 0.0942,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.87,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.66,
      "semantic_score": 0.278,
      "formant_ratio": 0.591,
      "token_count": 63,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " And after you've got the facts straight, it's time to move to the next phase, where you have insights and IDs to think about how you could respond faster, how you could prevent the problem, if there's any tools that you are missing. Any of these things that will make the future better."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 409840,
      "t1_ms": 425840,
      "confidence": 0.8862,
      "quality": 0.8862,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 21,
      "et_rms": 0.0940,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.84,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.220,
      "formant_ratio": 0.638,
      "token_count": 65,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " My advice is to pick an existing format for this. I like the blameless post mortem canvas. Everybody takes 5 to 10 minutes to write up a bunch of stickies in all of these boxes, except the summary, that's where you put your definition of failure, and then you move forward from there."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 425840,
      "t1_ms": 439840,
      "confidence": 0.9023,
      "quality": 0.9023,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 22,
      "et_rms": 0.0996,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.87,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.60,
      "semantic_score": 0.223,
      "formant_ratio": 0.611,
      "token_count": 55,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " After everybody has 1 to 3 stickies per section, it's grouping, deduplication, and explaining to each other so that everybody understands. And once you've got a feeling that you understand each other, it's time to create follow-up actions."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 439840,
      "t1_ms": 454840,
      "confidence": 0.9163,
      "quality": 0.9163,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 16,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 22,
      "et_rms": 0.0889,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.84,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.63,
      "semantic_score": 0.284,
      "formant_ratio": 0.626,
      "token_count": 74,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " In the canvas I've shown, most of these sections can create IDs for improvement. But what's the best one? If you have 10 IDs, you're not going to do them all. You probably won't have time for them. So which one has merit? Do you want to vote? Do you want to discuss? How do you want to proceed?"
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 454840,
      "t1_ms": 467840,
      "confidence": 0.8941,
      "quality": 0.8941,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 11,
      "et_rms": 0.0944,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.78,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.61,
      "semantic_score": 0.253,
      "formant_ratio": 0.597,
      "token_count": 60,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " This is where you discuss the IDs. This is where you decide I want to move forward to this one. And as a last thing, an action will only happen if it's concrete enough, it has an owner and a deadline. Set it at that time. And that's it."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 467840,
      "t1_ms": 478840,
      "confidence": 0.9269,
      "quality": 0.9269,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 11,
      "et_rms": 0.0975,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.77,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.55,
      "semantic_score": 0.231,
      "formant_ratio": 0.655,
      "token_count": 52,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " I hope you liked it. I hope this was useful. I'd like to hear from you. Have you ever ran a post mortem or a retro that felt like a post mortem because it was about a specific failure? How did it go?"
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 478840,
      "t1_ms": 480800,
      "confidence": 0.8552,
      "quality": 0.8243,
      "hcp_quality": 1.0000,
      "hallucination_flags": 0,
      "hcp_flagged_tokens": 1,
      "et_rms": 0.0864,
      "et_speech_frac": 0.63,
      "kiel_max_innovation": 0.55,
      "semantic_score": 0.081,
      "formant_ratio": 0.520,
      "token_count": 9,
      "speaker_turn": false,
      "text": " Please leave a comment and subscribe."
    },
    {
      "t0_ms": 480800,
